column1: #  Cut in parallax accuracy: Max error on distance < 1.5 pc.    After filtering on distance 7173 pairs remained
#  NO cut for RADIAL VELOCITY.
# Columns are:
#  1)  id_1         GAIA ID for primary
#  2)  id_2         GAIA ID for secondary
#  3)  ra_1         RA of primary star in degrees
#  4)  ra_err_1     error on right ascension in milliarcsec (mas)
#  5)  dec_1        DEC in degrees
#  6)  dec_err_1    error on DEC in mas
#  7)  ra_2         RA of secondary
#  8)  ra_err_2     error on RA of secundary in mas
#  9)  dec_2        DEC of secondary
# 10)  dec_err_2    error on DEC of secundary in mas
# 11)  d1           distance of primary in pc
# 12)  d1_err       error on distance in pc
# 13)  d2           distance of secondary in pc
# 14)  d2_err       error on distance in pc
# 15)  app_separ    Projected separation in arcsec
column2: this was required to be smaller than 2 pc.

column1: # 16)  radial_separ Separation along the radial direction (basically the difference of parallaxes) in pc. This was required to be smaller than 2pc.
# 17)  v1_ra        velocity from proper motion of primary in right ascension in km/s
# 18)  v1_ra_err    error on velocity along RA
# 19)  v1_dec       velocity from proper motion of primary along the declination
# 20)  v1_dec_err   error on velocity of primary along declination
# 21)  v2_ra        velocity from proper motion for secondary in km/s
# 22)  v2_ra_err    error on velocity along RA
# 23)  v2_dec       dec velocity of secundary in km/s
# 24)  v2_dec_err   error on velocity along DEC
# 25)  rv1         radial velocity of primary in km/s
# 26)  rv1_err     error on radial velocity in km/s
# 27)  rv2         radial velocity for secondary
# 28)  rv2_err     error on radial velocity
# 29)  m1           apparent magnitude of primary
# 30)  m2           app mag of secondary
# 31)  N2           number of stars (including the companion) in a cube of 2pc on a side centered on the primary
# 32)  N4           number of stars (including the companion) in a cube of 4pc on a side centered on the primary
